Mushroom

Source: R/bt_functions.R
bt_mushroom.Rd

Mushroom

Usage

bt_mushroom(
  bertin,
  data,
  top_values,
  bottom_values,
  bottom_tooltip,
  top_tooltip,
  ...
)

Arguments

bertin

map object

data

sf object EPSG:4326

top_values

top values

bottom_values

bottom values

bottom_tooltip

bottom tooltip

top_tooltip

top tooltip

...

other param

Value

a map object

Examples

library(sf)
world <- st_read(system.file("gpkg/world.gpkg", package = "bertin"),
                 layer = "world", quiet = TRUE)
africa <- subset(world, region == "Africa")
africa$pop_pct <- (africa$pop / sum(africa$pop, na.rm = TRUE)) * 100
africa$gdp_pct <- (africa$gdp / sum(africa$gdp, na.rm = TRUE)) * 100
bt_layer(data = africa, fill = "#808080") |>
  bt_mushroom(data = africa, top_values = "gdp_pct", bottom_values = "pop_pct") |>
  bt_draw()
